      <br>
      Customers are currently required to provide Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) authorisation when performing Bill Payment, Funds Transfer, eNETS or Remittance above a limit of S$1,000 via UOB Personal Internet Banking.</p>
<p> You can now choose your preferred threshold limit for invoking 2FA authorisation when performing Bill Payment, Funds Transfer, eNETS or Remittance via UOB Personal Internet Banking. <em><a href="http://www.uob.com.sg/personal/ebanking/pib/whatsnew.html" target="_blank" class="morelink">Click here</a> to view the limits available for selection</em>. </p>
      <p>You can also opt to receive SMS/email notification alerts when you perform transactions above the threshold limit. The threshold limit for receiving the notification alerts is also customisable. </p>
      <p>To change the threshold limit for 2FA authorisation and/or SMS/email alert notification, please click on<em><strong> Customer Service > Manage Notification and Authorisation</strong></em> upon login to UOB Personal Internet Banking.</p>
